District six residents say they're optimistic that the area will be redeveloped. CAPE TOWN - District Six residents say they're optimistic that the area will be redeveloped despite Rural Development and Land Reform Minister, Maite Nkoana-Mashabane. The minister told the Western Cape High Court that financial budget constraints caused the delay. READ: District Six land claimants want answers Nkoana-Mashabane asked public and private sector stakeholders to help make up the over R2-billion shortfall the department needs to redevelop the area. In total, 3,000 families are waiting to be returned to the area.